data.value:
Circular Measure ___________________________________________________________________
Angular Velocity = Angle / Time - Circular Acceleration given Radius of Circle and Velocity = (Velocity^2) / Radius - Circular Acceleration given Radius and Angular Velocity = Radius * (Angular Velocity^2) - Length of an Arc = Radius of circle * Angle at arc center - Period = (2 * Pi) / Angular Velocity - Velocity of a rotating object = Angular velocity * Radius of circle ___________________________________________________________________
Equations of Motion ___________________________________________________________________
Acceleration given Initial Velocity, Time and Final Velocity = (Final Velocity - Initial Velocity) / Time - Acceleration given Initial Velocity, Displacement and Time = 2(Displacement - (Initial velocity * Time)) / Time^2 - Distance travelled given Time, Initial Velocity and Acceleration = (Initial Velocity * Time) + (0.5 * Acceleration * Time^2) - Distance travelled given Inital Velocity, Final Velocity and Time = 0.5(Initial Velocity + Final Velocity) * Time - Final Velocity given Initial Velocity, Acceleration and Displacement = sqroot((Initial velocity^2) + (2 * Acceleration * Displacement)) - Final Velocity given Acceleration, Time and Initial Velocity = Initial Velocity + (Acceleration * Time) - Initial Velocity given Acceleration, Time and Final Velocity = Final Velocity - (Acceleration * Time) - Time taken given Initial Velocity, Acceleration and Final Velocity = (Final Velocity - Initial Velocity) / Acceleration
___________________________________________________________________
Gravitation ___________________________________________________________________
Density of a planet = (3 * Acceleration due to gravity) / (4 * Pi * Radius of Planet * Gravitational Constant) - Gravitational Force = (Gravitational Constant * mass * Mass) / Radius^2 - Gravitational Potential = - (Gravitational Constant * Mass of Planet) / Gravitational Potential - Mass of a planet = (Acceleration due to gravity * Radius of planet^2) / Gravitational Constant - Period of Satellite in its orbit = sqroot((4 * Pi^2 * Distance from center of planet^3) / (Acceleration due to Gravity * Radius^2)
___________________________________________________________________
Laws of Motion, Force and Momentum ___________________________________________________________________
Force acting on constant mass = Mass * Acceleration - Force due to momentum change = Momentum change / Time Taken - Gravitational Potential Energy = Mass * Acceleration due to gravity * Height change - Kinetic energy of an object = 0.5 * mass * Velocity^2 - Momentum of an object = Mass * Velocity of object - Work done = Force * Distance - Power = Work done / Time taken - Work done with force acting at an angle = Force * Cos(Angle of Force to Horizontal) * Displacement
___________________________________________________________________
Molecules and Matter, Elasticity ___________________________________________________________________
Energy stored in a wire = (0.5 * Modulus of Elasticity * Cross-sectional area * Extension^2) / Length of wire - Energy stored in a wire = 0.5 * Average force * Extension - Tensile Stress = Force / Area - Tensile Strain = Extension / Length of wire - Young Modulus of Elasticity = (Force / Area) / (Extension / Length of wire)
___________________________________________________________________
Simple Harmonic Motion ___________________________________________________________________
Acceleration of an object = -(Angular Velocity^2) * Distance of object from fixed point - Frequency of an oscillation = 1 / Period - Period of an oscillation = 1 / Frequency - Maximum Velocity = Angular velocity * Maximum amplitude - Period of simple harmonic motion = (2 * Pi) / Angular Velocity
___________________________________________________________________
Static bodies and fluids ___________________________________________________________________
Average pressure = Force / Area - Density of a substance = Mass / Volume - Pressure in a liquid = Density of liquid * Acceleration due to gravity * Depth below liquid surface - Torque = One force * Perpendicular distance between the two forces
